|Name gloss=receiving_of harm
|Description=Being harmed or damaged
|Comments=The Persian frame "daryaft-i sadamih" appears to have been translated directly from English; its wording rings as unnatural in Persian. A natural way of saying being harmed would be: "sadamih didan" [literally seeing damage/harm] or "sadamih khurdan" [lit. . eating harm]. The aforementioned Persian terms have been added to LU, but I propose that the frame be changed to "sadamih didan." As is, the frame would bear much fewer results while searched in any Persian-language corpus
